text: Châtelaudren-Plouagat is a commune in the Côtes-d'Armor department of Brittany in northwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Plouagat (the seat) and Châtelaudren.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Côtes-d'Armor department ==References== Category:Communes of Côtes-d'Armor Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Châtelaudren-Plouagat
